  "text": "www.ccsenet.org/ass Asian Social Science Vol. 11, No. 18; Firms in competitive industries are confronted by more liquidity risk than firms in non-competitive industries due to threats from potential rivals that attempt to enter these industries. Liquidity problems are also associated with the financial failure of many firms [CITATION_1] . For these reasons, competition increases business risk. In summary, firms in highly competitive markets are at greater business risk than those in less competitive markets.",
